{"name": "cfgstack", "metadata": {"name": "cfgstack", "version": "0.2.post2", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: GNU General Public License v3 (GPLv3)", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.10", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.12", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.8", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.9"], "home_page": "https://github.com/clearclaw/cfgstack", "license": "GPL-3.0-only", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["findfile_path", "logtool", "path", "addict", "pyyaml", "toml"], "summary": "Load stacks of JSON, TOML or YAML data", "upload_time": 1721614223}, "documentation": ["# CfgStack\n\nCfgStack is a configfile system reader. System? Yeah. In reading\nand parsing one file, CfgStack can be directed to go read other files\nand to incorporate their contents into the growing dataset.\n\n```\nCfgStack (\"somefile\")\n```\n\nAttempts to load the named file as JSON/YAML/TOML with default\nextensions of json/yaml/yml/toml (can be over-ridden). The loaded\nobject must be a dictionary. The \"data\" member of the resulting\nobject is an addict Dict of the loaded dataset. So far so simple.\n\n```\n_include_:\n  - file1\n  - file2\n_default_:\n  zero: 0\n  one: 1\nfoo:\n  this: that\n  zero: null\nvar: value\nbar:\n  _default_:\n    inner: inside_bar\n  inside:\n    oh: boy\n    yep: really\nbaz:\n  _include_:\n    - file3\n```\n\nA few things going on here:\n\n- \"\\_include\\_\" keys are assumed to list additional data files which\n  will be loaded and their contents merged with the dictionary at the\n  same level. If multiple files are listed, they will be applied in\n  order from the top down. Files are searched for in the CWD or\n  optionally in a list of passed paths.\n- \"\\_default\\_\" keys provide default key:value pairs for all\n  dictionary values at the current level\n\nNote that all includes are applied first, then all defaults. Higher\nlevel values override lower level values, across both includes and\ndefaults (includes first) and both for contents and data-type.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "cfgstack", "documentation": ["! /usr/bin/env python"], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "cfgstack.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "cfgstack.absolute_import", "xref": {"fqname": "__future__.absolute_import", "project": null}}, {"name": "cfgstack.CfgStack", "xref": {"fqname": "cfgstack.cfgstack.CfgStack", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack", "documentation": ["! /usr/bin/env python"], "functions": [{"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack._dictmerge", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "master", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "update", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["@logtool.log_call (log_args = False)"]}], "variables": [{"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack.DEFAULT_KEY", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack.INCLUDE_KEY", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack.OPEN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack.unicode", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack.OPEN", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [{"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack.CfgStack", "bases": ["object"], "methods": [{"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack.CfgStack.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fname", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "no_defaults", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "dirs", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "exts", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["pylint: disable=too-few-public-methods"]}, {"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack.CfgStack._load", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack.CfgStack._do_nesting", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "d", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "stack", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["@logtool.log_call (log_args = False, log_rc = False)"]}, {"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack.CfgStack._do_includes", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["@logtool.log_call (log_args = False, log_rc = False)"]}, {"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack.CfgStack._do_defaults", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["@logtool.log_call (log_args = False)"]}, {"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack.CfgStack.as_json", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "indent", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack.CfgStack.as_yaml", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "indent", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack.CfgStack.as_toml", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack.CfgStack.as_pretty", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack.CfgStack.dumps", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "form", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "indent", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cfgstack.cfgstack.CfgStack.write", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "fname", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "form", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Note that dictionaries inside of lists are not expanded with\nrespects to _default_ and _include_.  Only the immediate tree of\ndicts is munged.  The backing premise for this is that the purpose\nis configuration data, key value pairs, not arbitrary constructs."]}], "exports": []}]}